"en":{"1283–26 August 1346":"1283–26 August 1346","1270–Female":"1270–Deceased","1283–1346":"1283–1346","1285–Female":"1285–Deceased","1315–1388":"1315–1388","1322–1398":"1322–1398","1245–1301":"1245–1301","1258–1316":"1258–1316","1285":"1285","1283":"1283","1270":"1270","1316":"1316","1315":"1315","26 August 1346":"26 August 1346","1258":"1258","1346":"1346","1301":"1301","1322":"1322","1245":"1245","1388":"1388","1398":"1398","Crécy-en-Ponthieu, Abbeville, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Crécy-en-Ponthieu, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France","Lille, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Lille, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France","France":"France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"DE","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"WAVRIN","type":"LAST","meanings":["An old name. The same as Waring or Guerin, who came over with the Conqueror; a name probably connected with that of the Waernas or Wernas. the Varini or Verini, a people of the Elbe"],"variants":[]},{"name":"Jean","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Like   Jane   and   Joan  , a medieval variant of Old French <i>Je(h)anne</i>. Towards the end of the Middle Ages this form became largely confined to Scotland. In the 20th century it became more widely used in the English-speaking world and enjoyed a period of great popularity, but it is now out of fashion. Among numerous well-known and influential bearers are the British novelists  Jean Plaidy  (  Eleanor Hibbert ,  1910–93 ) and  Jean Rhys  (  Ella Gwendolen Rees Williams ,  1894–1979 ), British actress  Jean Simmons  (  1929–2010 ), and American-born actress  Jean Seberg  (  1938–79 ). It is also found as a variant spelling of the masculine name   Gene ."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."]},{"name":"Jeane","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Jean ."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Jean Robert BEAUSSART DE WAVRIN was born in 1283, in Lille, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France, his father, Robert DE WAVRIN DE SAINT VENANT III Brunel, was 38 and his mother, Mathilde de Lille, was 26. He had at least 2 sons with Marie De Cuinchy. He died on 26 August 1346, in Crécy-en-Ponthieu, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France, at the age of 63."},"et":{"1283–26 August 1346":"1283–26. august 1346","1270–Female":"1270–Surnud","1283–1346":"1283–1346","1285–Female":"1285–Surnud","1315–1388":"1315–1388","1322–1398":"1322–1398","1245–1301":"1245–1301","1258–1316":"1258–1316","1285":"1285","1283":"1283","1270":"1270","1316":"1316","1315":"1315","26 August 1346":"26. august 1346","1258":"1258","1346":"1346","1301":"1301","1322":"1322","1245":"1245","1388":"1388","1398":"1398","Crécy-en-Ponthieu, Abbeville, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Crécy-en-Ponthieu, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Lille, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Lille, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1283–26 August 1346":"1283–26. elokuuta 1346","1270–Female":"1270–Kuollut","1283–1346":"1283–1346","1285–Female":"1285–Kuollut","1315–1388":"1315–1388","1322–1398":"1322–1398","1245–1301":"1245–1301","1258–1316":"1258–1316","1285":"1285","1283":"1283","1270":"1270","1316":"1316","1315":"1315","26 August 1346":"26. elokuuta 1346","1258":"1258","1346":"1346","1301":"1301","1322":"1322","1245":"1245","1388":"1388","1398":"1398","Crécy-en-Ponthieu, Abbeville, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Crécy-en-Ponthieu, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Ranska","Lille, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Lille, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Ranska","France":"Ranska"},"fr":{"1283–26 August 1346":"1283–26 août 1346","1270–Female":"1270–Décédée","1283–1346":"1283–1346","1285–Female":"1285–Décédée","1315–1388":"1315–1388","1322–1398":"1322–1398","1245–1301":"1245–1301","1258–1316":"1258–1316","1285":"1285","1283":"1283","1270":"1270","1316":"1316","1315":"1315","26 August 1346":"26 août 1346","1258":"1258","1346":"1346","1301":"1301","1322":"1322","1245":"1245","1388":"1388","1398":"1398","Crécy-en-Ponthieu, Abbeville, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Crécy-en-Ponthieu, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France","Lille, Nord, Nord-Pa